SUMMARY:Journeys of the Water - STEAM in Local Native Traditions - Pt. 1
DESCRIPTION:All March long\, The FLIP Children’s Museum of Hillsboro will present the first in a new series of programs inspired by the traditions and knowledge of local Native cultures. Developed in collaboration with Native educators\, this program invites kids up to age 10 to explore the importance of waterways and canoes in Native life—from the past to the present. Children can build their own cardboard canoe\, help care for a wetland\, paddle down a river using our green screen\, and discover even more hands-on ways to learn through play. \n$10/Person\, Under Age 2 is Free \nEditor’s note: This event is a community submission.
URL:https://pdxparent.com/event-single/journeys-of-the-water-steam-in-local-native-traditions-pt-1/2026-03-22/
